<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10027403821366></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10027403821366><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=4063&mid=10027403821366>Regarding Price</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=4063&mid=10027403821366#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43695><span id=Scholar>Argfeld</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>25 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Oct 10th 2:59 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.66]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Almost any monk who is high enough level that he can afford to pay 25k for something will just get a group of his friends together and get this item for free.  As a matter of fact, that is what I am planning to do in the near future myself.  The only time you would see a monk pay 25k for this would be (A) if they purchased the platinum on E-Bay for their low level monk or (B) if they had obscene amounts of cash and were feeling too lazy to go after it themselves or (C) if they are one of those people that buys and sells stuff all the time in EC and makes 50k by the time they are level 10 (with 100 days played).  Twenty five thousand platinum can be spent to much greater effect on other, harder to get items.  Personally, I would probably pay about 3000 maximum for this item if I were going to buy it.  I am not putting down the item by the way.  It is very nice.  It just isn't worth 25k.<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
