<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99492488856479></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99492488856479><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=4063&mid=99492488856479>Not wandering</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=4063&mid=99492488856479#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=21572><span id= >millebj</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jul 12th 4:01 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Nezekezena and Phurzikon are NOT random spawns.  They do how every wander from their static spawn point after a few minutes or so(they never lived long enuff to wander tho :P) The spawn point i will post it tomorrow as i already logged for the night and forgot to write it down. When u first get to its static location tho if nothing is there u pull all surrounding mobs. eventually u will get the PH and at that point every 90 SECONDS one of them(Nez or Phur) or the ph will spawn. PH can be anything from a sarnak to a skeleton to a giant to a regular wurm and so on.  We were doin a mage epic and we killed the named spawns over 20 times.  Our group consisted of a mage an enchanter for mezzing a druid for snaring a bard for fear a monk and a cleric. We fear/snared everything and cleric didnt have to do a damn thing.  So if u cant get a cleric ur fine...just find some to fill the 6th spot and go hack em down!  BTW this is great exp. 90 seconds in between fights cant be beat. <br><br>Zager 51 monk <br>Cazic-Thule<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
